cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with language identification of social media text using deep learning models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of supervised learning and deep LSTM models, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of ensemble models and threshold techniques also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is a common task in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
